---
import MarketingLayout from "~/layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
const canonical = new URL("/privacy/", Astro.site).toString();
---
<MarketingLayout title="Privacy | Melbourne TVs" description="How Melbourne TVs handles quote enquiries, contact details and job photos." canonical={canonical}>
  <article class="legal"><h1>Melbourne TVs privacy notice</h1><p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 19 July 2026</p><h2>Information we collect</h2><p>When you request a quote, we may collect your name, email, mobile number, suburb, postcode, TV and wall details, preferred timing, notes, job photos and basic website attribution information.</p><h2>Why we use it</h2><p>We use the information to assess the enquiry, check service-area capacity, prepare a quote, coordinate with a suitable independent installer, respond to you, protect the form from misuse and keep an operational record of the enquiry.</p><h2>Who receives it</h2><p>Relevant enquiry details may be shared with a proposed independent installer so they can assess and quote the job. We also use service providers for website hosting, secure storage and business records, including Cloudflare and Google. We do not sell quote-enquiry information.</p><h2>Job photos</h2><p>Uploaded photos are intended for private job assessment. They are not published as portfolio or advertising content without separate permission.</p><h2>Marketing</h2><p>Marketing contact is optional and uses a separate consent choice. You can request that marketing messages stop at any time.</p><h2>Access, correction and deletion</h2><p>To ask about the personal information connected with your enquiry, request a correction or request deletion where applicable, email <a href="mailto:admin@melbournetvs.com">admin@melbournetvs.com</a>. We may retain information where reasonably required for security, dispute handling or legal obligations.</p></article>
</MarketingLayout>
<style>.legal{width:min(820px,calc(100% - 40px));margin:70px auto 100px;line-height:1.75}.legal h1{font-size:clamp(2.3rem,5vw,4rem)}.legal h2{margin-top:2.2rem}.legal p{color:#46554f}</style>
